# Testing and Regression Checks

- Add or update tests for bug fixes and critical business logic when test framework exists.
- For UI or template changes, verify empty, loading, error, and success states.
- Manually validate core flows impacted by the change before finalizing.
- Ensure no new PHP notices, warnings, or JS runtime errors are introduced.
- Keep tests deterministic; mock or isolate network-dependent behavior.
- Do not bypass failing checks without a clear, documented reason.
- Confirm changed routes/endpoints return expected status and payload shape.
